NON-BLOCKING FINDINGS (council follow-up needed)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

F1. WERNICKE SCHEMA DRIFT (pre-existing, NOT introduced by AO46)
    canonical_schemas.py declares:
      {ts, type, source, rms, n_samples, label, text,
       reality_hash, module_version}
    Real disk writes shape:
      {ts, speaker_id, proximity_meters, raw_english,
       stigmergic_intent, trace_id}
    AO46's c-tactile reads the REAL shape, so it works. But any
    strict assert_payload_keys("wernicke_semantics.jsonl", ...) call
    against real writes would crash. Reconcile.

F2. NEW HORMONE VARIANT NOT KNOWN TO DOWNSTREAM CASCADE
    OXYTOCIN_SOCIAL_BUFFERING is recognized only by c-tactile itself.
    swarm_vagal_tone, swarm_sympathetic_cortex, swarm_ribosome,
    swarm_parasympathetic_healing all hardcode OXYTOCIN_REST_DIGEST
    string match.
    IMPACT: c-tactile's stress neutralization works directly via
    ledger compaction (not via cascade signaling), so the lobe
    functions as designed. But if you WANT social-buffering oxytocin
    to ALSO veto sympathetic adrenaline, raise vagal tone, or throttle
    the ribosome, those 4 lobes need to add the new variant to their
    recognition lists.

F3. CORRUPT TIMESTAMP IN LIVE LEDGER (pre-existing, not AO46's fault)
    .sifta_state/endocrine_glands.jsonl tail line contains literal
    "$(date +%s)" instead of an evaluated number. Some earlier shell-
    heredoc append leaked the unevaluated variable. Will crash any
    consumer that does float(t["timestamp"]). Easy one-liner fix:
    sed-strip + re-append with real epoch.

F4. ENDOCRINE_GLANDS.JSONL WHITELISTED TWICE in swarm_oncology.py
    (lines 79 and 96). Functionally harmless; cosmetic dedup needed.

